TITLE:: PanolaMeter
summary:: the metric boundary hierarchy of a time signature
categories:: Notation, Utils
related:: Classes/PanolaMeterSplitter, Classes/PanolaDurationSpeller

DESCRIPTION::
PanolaMeter turns a time signature into a strength-ranked list of metric boundaries (each an offset in
quarterLength with an integer strength and a label), used by link::Classes/PanolaMeterSplitter:: to decide
where a note must break to respect the meter. Stronger boundaries (measure 100, the 4/4 half-measure 80,
compound beats 70, additive groups 75, ordinary beats 60, subdivisions 30-40) matter more. It handles
simple, compound (teletype::6/8:: teletype::9/8:: teletype::12/8::), and additive meters
(teletype::PanolaMeter(7, 8, [2,2,3])::). All offsets are exact link::Classes/PanolaRational::.



CLASSMETHODS::

METHOD:: new
build a meter for a time signature (numerator/denominator); pass groups only for an additive meter

ARGUMENT:: numerator
the time signature numerator (beats per measure)

ARGUMENT:: denominator
the time signature denominator (the beat note value: 4, 8, 16, ...)

ARGUMENT:: groups
for an additive meter, an Array of denominator-unit counts per group (e.g. teletype::[2,2,3]:: for 7/8); nil for simple and compound meters

returns:: a PanolaMeter
METHOD:: isCompound
whether a meter is compound: the numerator is divisible by 3 and greater than 3, and the denominator is 8 or 16

ARGUMENT:: num
the numerator

ARGUMENT:: den
the denominator

returns:: a Boolean

INSTANCEMETHODS::

METHOD:: numerator
the time signature numerator (the number of beats per measure), e.g. 4 in 4/4

returns:: an Integer
METHOD:: denominator
the time signature denominator (the beat note value), e.g. 4 in 4/4

returns:: an Integer
METHOD:: groups
for an additive meter, the Array of denominator-unit counts per group (e.g. teletype::[2,2,3]:: for 7/8); nil for simple and compound meters

returns:: an Array of Integers, or nil
METHOD:: measureLengthQL
the length of one measure in quarterLength

returns:: a link::Classes/PanolaRational::
METHOD:: boundaries
the strength-ranked metric boundary list: Events of the form teletype::(offsetQL: PanolaRational, strength: Integer, label: String):: sorted by offset, one per offset (the strongest is kept at each)

returns:: an Array of boundary Events sorted by offset
METHOD:: pr_init
initialize the meter: store the numerator, denominator and groups, compute the measure length, and build the boundary list

ARGUMENT:: num
the numerator

ARGUMENT:: den
the denominator

ARGUMENT:: grps
the additive groups Array, or nil

returns:: this PanolaMeter
METHOD:: pr_unit
the quarterLength of one denominator-unit (teletype::4 / denominator::), e.g. 0.5 for an eighth in an /8 meter

returns:: a link::Classes/PanolaRational::
METHOD:: pr_build
build the strength-ranked boundary list: add the measure-start and measure-end boundaries, then the interior boundaries for a simple, compound, or additive meter, then deduplicate and sort

returns:: an Array of boundary Events sorted by offset
METHOD:: pr_simple
append the beat boundaries (with the 4/4 half-measure and 2/x weightings) and the half-unit subdivisions for a simple meter to the boundary list

ARGUMENT:: bs
the List of boundaries being built (mutated in place)

ARGUMENT:: unit
the quarterLength of one denominator-unit

returns:: nothing meaningful (it appends to bs)
METHOD:: pr_compound
append the compound-beat boundaries (every three denominator-units) and the eighth-subbeat boundaries for a compound meter to the boundary list

ARGUMENT:: bs
the List of boundaries being built (mutated in place)

ARGUMENT:: unit
the quarterLength of one denominator-unit

returns:: nothing meaningful (it appends to bs)
METHOD:: pr_additive
append the additive-group boundaries (at the end of each group except the last) and the within-group subdivisions for an additive meter (following the groups Array) to the boundary list

ARGUMENT:: bs
the List of boundaries being built (mutated in place)

ARGUMENT:: unit
the quarterLength of one denominator-unit

returns:: nothing meaningful (it appends to bs)
METHOD:: pr_sortUnique
deduplicate the boundaries by offset (keeping the strongest boundary at each offset) and return them sorted by ascending offset

ARGUMENT:: bs
the List of boundaries to deduplicate

returns:: an Array of boundary Events sorted by offset

